</DOCHDR>
<html><head><title>Duplantier:  ANTI-POVERTY PROGRAM SUPPORTS LEFTIST CAUSES</title></head><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/background.jpg"><a href="/townhall/columnists/"><img align="right" vspace="10" src="/townhall/columnists/thcolm.gif"></a><center><h4>BEHIND THE HEADLINES </h4><i>Commentary from America's Future, Inc.<br><a href="/townhall/columnists/duplbio.html">F.R. Duplantier</a> <br>November 16, 1995<br></i><hr><h2>Anti-Poverty Program Supports Leftist Causes</h2></center><P>




[Every year on the weekend before Thanksgiving, American Catholics 
are asked to contribute to their Church's Campaign for Human 
Development (known as CHD). More and more Catholics are declining 
to do so, however, as they learn about the Campaign's strange support for 
radical, left-wing organizations.]
<p>
The Capital Research Center in Washington DC reports that the 
Campaign for Human Development. the antipoverty program of the 
American Catholic bishops. is not at all what the faithful have been led 
to believe it is. If American Catholics had had any idea where the money 
really goes, they would not have dumped more than $230 million into 
the CHD collection baskets over the past 25 years. "What they are not 
told. and what the bureaucrats at CHD do not want them to know." the 
Capital Research Center charges. "is that most of CHD's money goes to 
support liberal activists who use it teach people how to organize and 
agitate for more government spending programs."
<p>
Adding insult to injury. "CHD-funded activists are often openly 
disdainful of the teachings of the Catholic Church. Whose offerings they 
gladly accept." CHD's 25th anniversary conference, held three months 
ago in Chicago. provided a good example of the persons and policies 
unwittinglv promoted by pious parishioners. Conference participants 
were treated to speeches By "a Marxist college professor. pro-abortion 
and pro-gay rights activists. and a strident opponent of school choice."
<p>
The Campaign for Human Development "operates on the same 
assumptions as Lyndon Johnson's War on Poverty," providing no 
incentives for "individual striving and responsibility." According to the 
Capital Research Center. "Rather than offer the poor the example of 
success, and guidance in achieving it. CHD explains why poverty is the 
system's fault and teaches how to radicalize institutions." Despite its 
claims of nonpartisanship, "almost all of its activities fall on the left -- 
often the far-left -- side of the ideological spectrum. CHD-funded groups 
invariably favor public policies that require state intervention and 
decision-making. And these build support for their positions by resorting 
to the rhetoric of class consciousness and the tactics of social conflict."
<p>
The Capital Research Center contends that "CHD has established a long 
track record of funding groups whose activities many Catholics would 
find repugnant." It also has a history of responding to the problems of 
society with solutions that "preclude genuine Christian social action. By 
concentrating on tried-and-failed methods of victimization and blame, 
CHD undermines the individual's capacity for spiritual, moral, and social 
renewal."
<p>
The Capital Research Center implores the American bishops "to initiate 
a desperately-needed overhaul of the Campaign for Human 
Development," urging them to "exercise active oversight, not rubber-
stamp decisions by CHD professional staff." If nothing else, the bishops 
should be "honest with parishioners about the aims and activities of 
CHD." In the meantime, if American Catholics want to know what 
they're contributing to, they'll have to conduct their own investigations.

<p>                           <P><i>Behind The Headlines is produced by America's Future, a nonprofit educational organization dedicated to the preservation of our free enterprise system and our constitutional form of government. For a free transcript of this broadcast, write: America's Future, 7800 Bonhomme, St. Louis, Missouri 63105.</i><p><br><br><center><br><a href="/townhall/tbut.map"><img src="/townhall/tbut.gif" ismap border="0"></a></center></body></html>
