<html><HEAD><TITLE>Duplantier: PC ON CAMPUS HINDERS PURSUIT OF TRUTH</title></head><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/background.jpg"><a href="/townhall/columnists/"><img align="right" vspace="10" src="/townhall/columnists/thcolm.gif"></a><center><h4>BEHIND THE HEADLINES </h4><i>Commentary from America's Future, Inc.<br><a href="/townhall/columnists/duplbio.html">F.R. Duplantier</a> <br>November 30, 1995<br></i><hr><h2>PC on Campus Hinders Pursuit of Truth</h2></center><P>
[The search for truth is getting to be a risky business.  Just ask any  
college student who's run afoul of the thought police on campus.]   
  <p>
There's no longer any use in denying it. The temples of learning have   
become indoctrination centers. Academic freedom has given way to mass   
hysteria. A bizarre misanthropic cult now reigns supreme on American   
college campuses. "Political correctness has been used to enforce   
conformity and to stifle debate," say Peter Duignan and L.H. Gann of the   
Hoover Institution. "Censorship is practiced in a variety of ways. through   
the planned disruption of meetings, the use of so-called speech codes, and   
the coercive use of sensitivity training or suspension from school.   
<p>Indirect censorship is also practiced through the selection of assigned   
reading and also through hiring practices."  
  <p>
The puppets of political correctness reject the European focus of   
American history, ignoring the fact that "the United States is, for the   
greater part, a demographic and cultural extension of Europe beyond the   
Atlantic. About four-fifths of the US population derives from European   
stock," say Duignan and Gann. "The United States owes a cultural debt to   
almost every land under the sun," they concede. "But no other country   
influenced the United States as much as Great Britain." Our language, our   
literature, our legal system, our system of government, our ethical system   
-- all have British origins.   
  <p>
The PC crowd insists on a growing array of ethnic studies programs to   
remedy the alleged racial bias of Western scholarship. They're unwilling   
to accept the fact that the United States is a product of Western   
civilization. with pronounced European characteristics -- characteristics   
that include a unique appreciation for cultures other than its own. <p>"Far   
from being one of the world's most oppressive societies, the United States   
is the most successful multiracial and multiethnic state in existence," say   
Duignan and Gann. "No other country attracts as many immigrants and   
bestows its citizenship on so many newcomers. No other country is   
ethnically more varied."  
  <p>
Purveyors of political correctness claim that the West has had a uniformly   
negative impact on lesser developed countries. On the contrary.   
"mainland has gained in the long run by the Western conquest of the New   
World and by the consequent emergence of new nations," say Duignan   
and Gann. "Modern industrial civilization allows not only higher   
economic productivity! than its early predecessors but also an infinitely   
larger population and higher material well-being and a longer life," not to   
mention "an infinitely larger number of choices."  
  <p>
In their eagerness to condemn the United States as a racist and sexist   
society. the PC partisans willingly ignore the numerous alternative   
explanations for economic inequities -- such as the median age of ethnic   
groups. cultural and genetic differences. and so on. They also maintain   
that America is not the free country we have all been "brainwashed" to   
believe it is. That they themselves are the ones who have been   
brainwashed. that the PC movement itself threatens the liberties of all   
Americans -- such ironies are lost on this humorless horde.  
<p>                           <P><i>Behind The Headlines is produced by America's Future, a nonprofit educational organization dedicated to the preservation of our free enterprise system and our constitutional form of government. For a free transcript of this broadcast, write: America's Future, 7800 Bonhomme, St. Louis, Missouri 63105.</i><p><br><br><center><br><a href="/townhall/tbut.map"><img src="/townhall/tbut.gif" ismap border="0"></a></center></body></html>
